                <h3>My One House Match Suggestions</h3>
                <p><strong>Personal data will only be stored on the site temporarily until the review process has begun.</strong></p>
                <p>Thank you for your interest in becoming a bidder with One House At A Time. Please complete the following application. You can type directly into the fields on the form and submit, or print it out if you prefer. Also, you can print a blank form and fill it in manually. Then, scan/email, fax, or mail the completed form and supporting documents our office.</p>
                <p>Please contact us with any questions for assistance at: office@onehousebaltimore.org or call in at 410-467-1826</p>
                <p>Note: The completed application and required documentation must be submitted no later that five (5) business days before an auction in order to participate as a bidder in that auction.</p>
                <h3>Applicants Must Demonstrate:</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Financial ability: Submit documentation showing assets to support the purchase and rehabilitation of the vacant property within 12 months of the date of settlement.</li>
                    <li>Business experience: Demonstrate thorough knowledge of and/or experience in real estate transactions and the rehabilitation of vacant property. Include addresses in Baltimore City (or if none, list other Maryland jurisdictions) where renovation work was completed with permits.</li>
                    <li>Good standing: If Applicant (or its affiliates/related parties) owns property in Maryland including Baltimore City, then the applicant and its properties must be in good standing which includes but is not limited to: not having outstanding or unresolved housing code or building code enforcement actions/notices. Note: Prior ownership of property in Baltimore City (or Maryland) is not a prerequisite to qualifying.</li>
                </ol>
                <p>To verify good standing, all applicants must disclose:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>All properties owned, in whole or in part, by the individuals and/or affiliates/related parties including members of the individual's immediate family, including LLCs owned in whole or in part by said persons.</li>
                    <li>All properties owned, in whole or in part, by the affiliates/related parties including members, principals, partners, and/or resident agents of the corporate entity, including LLCs owned in whole or in part by said corporate entity.</li>
                    <li>Any and all court actions or code enforcement actions involving a) Baltimore City and b) all other Maryland jurisdictions regarding any real property owned in whole or in part by the individuals or corporate entities or affiliates/related parties.</li>
                    <li>Any and all relationships with any individuals and/or corporate entities that have been disqualified by One House At A Time in the past.</li>
                </ul>
